      "id": "2024727586543407613",
      "text": "RT @XFreeze: Elon Musk is hosting the 5th annual Not-a-Boring Student Competition\n\nThe Boring Company can already dig tunnels faster than m…",
      "created_at": "Fri Feb 20 06:07:28 +0000 2026",
      "lang": "en",
      "media": [],
      "retweet": {
        "id": "2024638379518722300",
        "text": "Elon Musk is hosting the 5th annual Not-a-Boring Student Competition\n\nThe Boring Company can already dig tunnels faster than most companies:\n\n• Traditional tunnel boring machines can take many months to advance a single mile\n•  The latest Prufrock machines target over one mile per week\n\nTo push this even further, Elon is challenging engineering students from different universities to build advanced tunnel-boring machines\n\nThis March, more than 120 students from 8 universities across 3 countries will compete to beat the snail at the company's R&D headquarters in Bastrop, Texas\n\nThis continues to push the boundaries of tunneling technology",
